menu "Identity Obfuscation"

    config OPSEC_IDENTITY_SPOOF_MAC
        bool "Spoof WiFi station MAC address"
        default y if WOL_PROFILE_HARDENED
        default n
        help
            Derives a locally-administered MAC address from the chip's
            burned-in eFuse base MAC using esp_derive_local_mac().

            The resulting MAC has bit 1 of the first octet set (locally
            administered bit) and does NOT resolve to Espressif in any
            OUI lookup table. This prevents passive network scanners from
            fingerprinting the device as an ESP32.

            Note: esp_wifi_set_mac() must be called while the WiFi driver
            is in INIT state (before esp_wifi_start()). The identity
            component handles this ordering automatically.

            Note: Cannot be enabled on ESP32-S2 and some C-series chips
            where the MAC is derived differently. Check your target's
            documentation if the build fails with ESP_ERR_NOT_SUPPORTED.

    config OPSEC_IDENTITY_FAKE_HOSTNAME
        bool "Use obfuscated DHCP hostname"
        default y if WOL_PROFILE_HARDENED
        default n
        help
            Replaces the default DHCP hostname (which contains "espressif"
            or "esp32") with a plausible consumer-device string derived
            from a hash of the chip MAC.

            Format: <PREFIX><6-char-hex-suffix>
            Example: "NETGEAR-A3F19C"

            The prefix is set by OPSEC_IDENTITY_HOSTNAME_PREFIX below.

    config OPSEC_IDENTITY_HOSTNAME_PREFIX
        string "Fake hostname prefix"
        default "NETGEAR-"
        depends on OPSEC_IDENTITY_FAKE_HOSTNAME
        help
            The prefix prepended to the 6-character hex MAC hash suffix.
            Choose something plausible for your network environment
            (e.g. "TP-LINK-", "DLINK-", "HUAWEI-").

            Keep it under 16 characters so the full hostname stays within
            the 32-character DHCP hostname limit.

endmenu
